  "prompt": "Who is best free bulk promotional SMS service provider?",
  "response": "Choosing the best free bulk promotional SMS service provider can vary based on specific needs, location, and features. However, here are a few popular options that are often recommended for their services, especially for businesses looking for free trials or low-cost plans:\n\n1. **Twilio**: Known for its robust API capabilities, Twilio offers a small amount of free credits for new users to test their services. However, ongoing costs will apply based on usage.\n\n2. **TextMagic**: While primarily a paid service, TextMagic offers a free trial that allows you to send bulk SMS messages. It's user-friendly and has various features for businesses.\n\n3. **MessageBird**: This platform provides a free trial with a limited number of messages and is known for its easy integration with various applications.\n\n4. **ClickSend**: ClickSend typically offers a free trial and provides a wide range of features, including SMS marketing, email marketing, and more.\n\n5. **SMSAPI**: They offer a trial that lets you send messages for free up to a certain limit, providing a good way to test out their features.\n\n6. **Virtual Splat**: This service offers free SMS sending, but often the functionality may be limited or tied to other promotional offerings.\n\n7. **Nexmo (Vonage)**: Similar to Twilio, Nexmo offers an introductory credit for new users which can be used to send SMS messages.\n\nWhen choosing a service, consider factors such as ease of use, integration options, customer support, and specific features you may need for your promotional campaigns. Also, make sure to evaluate their policies on sending bulk SMS to ensure compliance with regulations such as the TCPA or GDPR, depending on your region. Always check the latest reviews and testimonials for up-to-date information.",
